st.write(st.session_state)



------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#######  Your 5 Simple Rules to Remember âœ‹


Rule 1: Always CHECK before using
if "variable_name" not in st.session_state:
    st.session_state.variable_name = "starting_value"
ğŸ‘† ALWAYS do this FIRST for every variable!

Rule 2: Store like a Dictionary -- both ways useful but i like 2nd method .name
st.session_state["name"] = "John"  # Method 1
st.session_state.name = "John"     # Method 2
Both work! I'll use Method 2 (dot) as it's simpler.

Rule 3: Get values like a Dictionary
current_name = st.session_state.name

Rule 4: Update when inputs change
# User types in text box
user_input = st.text_input("Type here")
if user_input != st.session_state.my_text:
    st.session_state.my_text = user_input  # Update!

Rule 5: Display from Session State
st.write(f"Value stored: {st.session_state.my_text}")


